# Alco Project Rules

## Check README First

When you're about to start a new task, make sure to check the README.md file first to understand the project structure.

```cursor-rule
match: task|implement|create|add|develop
suggest: Please review README.md first to understand the project framework, structure, and components.
```

## Math Operations

When dealing with mathematics or spatial operations, first review the existing implementations in the Math directory.

```cursor-rule
match: math|vector|matrix|transform|rotation|quaternion|spatial
globs: "**/*.cs"
suggest: Check Src/Alco/Math/ directory for existing mathematical implementations before proceeding.
```

## Alco.Editor Build Check

After editing code in the Alco.Editor project, make sure to build the project to check for compilation errors.

```cursor-rule
match: Alco\.Editor
globs: "**/*.cs,**/*.axaml"
suggest: After editing, run 'dotnet build Editor/Alco.Editor/Alco.Editor.csproj' to check for compilation errors.
```

## HLSL Shader Validation

After editing HLSL shader files, validate them to check for compilation errors.

```cursor-rule
match: \.hlsl|shader|HLSL
globs: "**/*.hlsl"
suggest: After editing HLSL shaders, run 'dotnet test Test/Alco.Engine.Test/Alco.Engine.Test.csproj --filter "FullyQualifiedName=Alco.Engine.Test.ValidateShader.ValidateAllShaders"' to validate all shaders.
``` 